Key Match Events: Mitchell Duke scored a second-half goal to put the Socceroos two up.
Bahrain conceded an own goal in the first half.
Sam Silvera was given his first start for Australia.
Joe Gauci made a fantastic save in the 68th minute.
Craig Goodwin received a yellow card in the 63rd minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Graham Arnold described the match as perfect preparation for the Asian Cup.
Craig Goodwin praised the Socceroos' patience in their 2-0 win.
Mitchell Duke was pleased with the important minutes gained in the Bahrain test.
